-- Corpbanca Unit in U.S. Plans to Sell Certificates of Deposit
-- B y   S e b a s t i a n   B o y d
-- 2012-05-04T19:51:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/corpbanca-unit-in-u-s-plans-to-sell-certificates-of-deposit.html
The New York-based unit of  Corpbanca (CORPBANC) ,
Chile’s fifth-largest lender by assets, set up a $750 million
program to sell certificates of deposit to investors in the
U.S., according to an e-mailed statement.  Corpbanca will be the first Chilean lender to sell the
short-term debt instruments, the New York office’s general
manager, Fernando Burgos, said in the statement.  JPMorgan Chase & Co. will manage the program.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sebastian Boyd in Santiago at 
 sboyd9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
